 "metadata": {
  "title": "The physical substrate — semiconductor supply chain, global logistics/shipping, and the standards-setting bodies that govern them",
  "generated": "2026-06-21",
  "status": "company roles, ownership stakes, market shares, chokepoints, and standards-committee facts are FACT (web-verified); the 'chokepoint concentration = systemic + geopolitical leverage' reading is graded interpretation; no intent imputed",
  "frame": "The AI bubble the corpus maps rests on a PHYSICAL substrate it under-drew: (1) a semiconductor supply chain that narrows to single points of failure (one EUV maker, ASML; one optics maker inside it, ZEISS; one advanced foundry, TSMC; one packaging bottleneck, CoWoS); (2) a global logistics/shipping network that runs through a handful of maritime chokepoints; and (3) the standards-setting bodies (ISO/IEC/IEEE/IMDRF/...) that quietly write the rules every product must meet. Same lenses: chokepoint concentration, dual-use, Sun Tzu (control the terrain/deny foreknowledge), composition-fallacy guard (an industry ACTING is not an industry with one MIND), and grading. Ties to macro-pqc-chips, fin-google-amazon-anthropic-meta (the chip cohort), macro-critical-minerals (upstream materials), spec-cross-system-contagion, and spec-quantum-computing-competitive-landscape (GlobalFoundries fab chokepoint).",
  "grading": "fact | contested | weak | unsupported"
 },
 "the_lithography_chokepoint": "The narrowest point in the modern economy. ASML (Netherlands) is the SOLE maker of EUV lithography — no advanced (<7nm) logic exists without it. Inside ASML is a deeper chokepoint: Carl Zeiss SMT exclusively makes the EUV optics/mirrors (polished to picometer flatness, multilayer-coated to nanometer precision — objects no one else can build); ASML owns a 24.9% / EUR1B stake in Zeiss SMT and calls it its most important strategic partner. Cymer (an ASML subsidiary) makes the EUV light source. High-NA EUV (NA>0.5, the EXE line) extends scaling further. EUV is EXPORT-CONTROLLED — ASML cannot sell EUV to China (Dutch + US restrictions), the single most consequential tech-sanction lever. Nikon/Canon make only DUV (Canon is pushing nanoimprint/NIL as an alt path). grade: fact.",
 "the_foundry_and_packaging_chokepoint": "TSMC (Taiwan) fabricates ~90% of the world's most-advanced logic; the geographic concentration on Taiwan is the defining geopolitical risk of the AI era (Taiwan-Strait exposure). But the ACUTE bottleneck in 2025-26 is NOT wafers (2nm/N2) — it is ADVANCED PACKAGING: TSMC's CoWoS (2.5D) families (CoWoS-S/-L) are fully booked with 52-78 week lead times; Nvidia holds >70% of CoWoS-L capacity, with Google/Apple/Meta/Anthropic/OpenAI/ByteDance fighting for the rest. The wafer-fab equipment (WFE) oligopoly — Applied Materials, Lam Research, Tokyo Electron, KLA — and the materials majors (Shin-Etsu, SUMCO for wafers; JSR, Tokyo Ohka for photoresist) sit upstream. HBM memory (SK Hynix, Samsung, Micron; standardized by JEDEC) is the other AI bottleneck. EDA tools (Synopsys, Cadence, Siemens EDA) + Arm IP are the design chokepoint, also export-controlled to China. SMIC is China's sanctioned foundry (7nm via DUV multi-patterning). grade: fact.",
 "the_logistics_layer": "Physical goods (chips, datacenter hardware, everything) move through a concentrated maritime network: the ocean-carrier oligopoly (Maersk, MSC, CMA CGM, Hapag-Lloyd, COSCO, ONE) and the 3PL majors (DHL, Kuehne+Nagel, DSV, DB Schenker, FedEx, UPS, C.H. Robinson) funnel through a few CHOKEPOINTS — the Suez Canal (Red Sea/Houthi disruptions rerouting around Africa), the Panama Canal (drought-constrained), the Strait of Malacca, the Strait of Hormuz, and the Taiwan Strait. A disruption at any one cascades into cost, lead-time, and inventory shocks (the just-in-time fragility the 2021-22 supply shock exposed). grade: fact (the firms + chokepoints); the systemic-fragility read is interpretation.",
 "the_standards_layer": "The least-visible power: standards-setting bodies write the rules every product must meet, and whoever writes the standard shapes the market (soft-power leverage; China's 'Standards 2035' explicitly targets this terrain). ISO + IEC run the joint committee ISO/IEC JTC 1, whose subcommittees include SC 42 (Artificial Intelligence — ~45 published standards, the AI-governance battleground) and SC 27 (IT security/the PQC standards channel). Adjacent: IEEE, ITU + ETSI + 3GPP (telecom/mobile), SEMI + JEDEC (semiconductor/memory), ANSI (US), BIPM (metrology), Codex Alimentarius (food). Medical devices: the Global Harmonization Task Force (GHTF) was succeeded by the IMDRF (International Medical Device Regulators Forum), aligning ISO 13485 (QMS) + ISO 14971 (risk) across regulators. NIST feeds international AI + cryptography standards. The lens: standards are chokepoints of LEGITIMACY — controlling them is controlling the terrain (Sun Tzu) without firing a shot. grade: fact (bodies + scopes); the soft-power framing is labeled interpretation.",
 "the_composition_caveat": "An industry coordinating around a standard, or concentrating at a chokepoint, is institutional ACTION — it does NOT imply a unitary industry MIND or conspiracy (composition-fallacy guard). The concentration emerges from economies of scale, decades of unrepeatable co-development (ASML/Zeiss), and network effects — structural causes, not necessarily designed ones. The finding is fragility + leverage, not intent.",
